 The family of a former Minister, late Dr. Hassan Lawal Nelly, has given their votes to the All Progressives Congress (APC) presidential candidate, Asiwaju Bola Ahmed Tinubu, in their hometown of Keffi in Keffi local government area, Nasarawa State. Tinubu gained the highest number of votes against his counterparts in Keffi local government area. Atiku Abubakar of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) received 13,102 votes, while Peter Obi of the Labour Party received 9,406 votes, making the APC candidate the winner with 13,564 votes. Late Dr. Hassan Lawal was a Nigerian politician, who served as the Minister of Labour, Minister of Health and Minister of Works and Housing respectively at different times for seven years. The late Minister served under President Olusegun Obasanjo and late President Ummaru Musa Yarâ€™Adua administrations.